      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be verified under a documented SQA plan with version control and regression testing at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used under an ISO 9001-certified SQA framework. Version control via Git, regression test suite of 47 benchmark cases executed at each release. All tests pass. SQA documentation archived in the project repository."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark comparisons at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent code verification confirmed against FDA benchmark nozzle and backward-facing step cases. Velocity profiles match analytical and DNS reference solutions within 2% RMS error. Power-law hemolysis sub-model verified against Giersiepen et al. analytical solution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI must be below 3% for primary QoIs across all operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. GCI values for NIH range from 1.8% to 2.6% across all five operating points, satisfying the 3% threshold. Fine-grid solution (19.2M cells) adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be sufficiently documented to enable replication and comparison.",
      "rationale": "Morrison et al. (2020) experimental protocol documents fluid temperature (37°C), hematocrit (33%), anticoagulation protocol, and measurement uncertainty for NIH (±5%). Boundary conditions applied in CFD match reported experimental inlet/outlet conditions within measurement uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric between CFD predictions and experimental data must be defined and applied consistently.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute relative error (MARE) used as primary comparison metric. MARE = 8.3% across five operating points, below the 15% acceptance threshold. U95 validation uncertainty computed per ASME V&V 20 and found to be 11.2%, confirming model adequacy at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
