      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, RH) must directly correspond to the regulatory decision quantities.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary regulatory QoI for hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. RH < 1 is the acceptance criterion for predicate device comparison. Both QoIs are computed directly from CFD output and compared against experimental measurements and predicate device data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
